frameDefinitions: This frame has to do with the repetition (and especially the frequency of repetition) of an event.
An Agent acts in a certain Manner either generally or under some particular Circumstances.
The universe is considered through a teleological perspective and natural phenomena are seen to exist for the purpose of fulfilling some ultimate aim.
A linguistic Form has a particular Meaning, possibly restricted to a particular Context.
An Entity represents some Phenomenon through its existence and/or defining characteristics.
A mathematical expression Expression_1 has a relationship with another mathematical expression Expression_2.
frameExamples: China will have to face a high <t>frequency</t> of sand storms in the years to come.
He pledges to  <t>conduct</t> himself  with honesty and humility.
The <t>PURPOSE</t> of the sun is to provide energy
'Unicorn' <t>denotes</t> a mythological horse with a horn on its head.
A bear <t>symbolizes</t> strength in some cultures.
The <t>FORMULA</t> of a line can be given in slope-intercept form
listRoleDefinitions: This role is used for any (bounded) <fen>Event</fen> whose frequency or iteration is described.
The extent to which the actually observed rate of occurrence of the <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Salient_entity</fen> differs from the expected rate.
The <fen>Interval</fen> is a noun modified by the target word. The target word specifies the frequency of the <fen>Interval</fen> .
The <fen>Time_span</fen> is the length of time of the <fen>Interval</fen>. This role is incorporated by most of the lexical units in this frame.
The number of times per unit of real or scanning time that an <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is encountered.
An entity which the implicit cognizer encounters with the specified frequency.
The frequency feature of the <fen>Event</fen> or <fen>Salient_entity</fen> that is under discussion. All the lexical units in this frame incorporate this frame element.
The Time when the Event has a particular frequency.
This role marks expressions that denote the person whose conduct is being evaluated.
This role marks expressions that characterize the way that the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves in a certain way.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> exhibits their behavior.
An entity that was not created by a living thing that is conceptualized to exist to fulfill some <fen>Goal</fen>.
The ultimate aim of the <fen>Apparatus</fen>.
<fen>Form</fen> is the formal pole of a linguistic sign.
<fen>Meaning</fen> is the sense of a linguistic <fen>Form</fen>.
<fen>Referent</fen> identifies an object in the real (or a hypothetical) world that a linguistic expression is used to talk about.
The event, idea, or emotion evoked by the <fen>Entity</fen>.
An object that has some association with a <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The time period in which the representing occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the representing event occurs.
In an equation that has more terms on one side than the other, <fen>Expression_1</fen> is the side of the equation with fewer terms.
In an equation that has more terms on one side than the other, <fen>Expression_2</fen> is the side of the equation that has more terms.
listRoleExamples: The country has been struck by frequent <fex>economic crises</fex>.
The Crested Lark (Galerida cristata) is  <fex>very</fex> frequent from the coastal plain to the mountains.
You have to renew the license every <fex>year</fex> .
The state government spends its fiscal year 2006 budget of $23.4 billion at a rate <fex>of $742 per second</fex>.
It costs about US$2.50 to travel 200km (124 mi), but <fex>buses</fex> are infrequent and only one or two buses a day service most routes.
These exposures were likely to be intermittent <fex>in frequency</fex> occurring only when workers were participating in activities at these specific areas.
They stood together and posed for the pass, Alleyne relaxed and smiling , a tall , angular man who carried himself <fex>with natural elegance</fex> .
She knew that she had behaved badly <fex>last night</fex>

Sometimes an offender may be placed at a Probation hostel because they have committed
a serious offence or have behaved badly <fex>at an independent hostel</fex>
